race.comment: SAVAGE DANCER (8) has been a little disappointing since a bold first-up effort, beaten 3.1L behind a dominant winner last time out as the $2.05 favourite. Pike sticks with her as she returns to Ascot today and if she can settle closer this time around, she can return to winning ways. GREAT PROMISE (9) got the job done fresh at Belmont when setting the tempo throughout, scoring by a length in a good performance. She turned in a strong rating there and if she can handle the rise in trip second-up, she'll be hard to reel in once again. IMAPAGETHREE GIRL (5) was only 0.6L off the winner last start following a very nice trial coming into this campaign. Drops back in grade now from a good draw and she looks a live chance with the blinkers going back on. PRINCESS IN RED (3) stuck on well at Belmont fresh after a nice trial coming into this campaign. 3kg claim comes in handy and she can improve. BLUE CAN TALK (6) needs some luck but has a few ratings that can see her feature.
